Motorists who still need to renew their driver's licences have been given two more weeks to do so. The deadline has been extended to the 15th of April. Layton Beard from the Automobile Association of South Africa, spoke to eNCA's Dan Moyane on this. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Transport Department has announced that licensing centres across the country will be operating over the weekend. Minister Fikile Mbalula says additional capacity has been introduced to address the sluggish pace of renewals. READ:Â Deadline to renew driving licences extended During the weekend, motorists will be assisted whether they have a booking or not.
Mbalula says more than half the motorists, whose licenses expired during the height of the pandemic, have still not applied to renew them. He adds that the department has managed to reduce the backlog to 1.4-million. Mbalula announced a final extension to the grace period yesterday. Motorists now have until 15 April to renew their licences.